src=\"/assets/faces/big/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-08-09T04:32:34.000Z","msg":"冇啦 有得救我地唔洗係到討論<br />\n五毛又多 親中拎著數嘅人又多<br />\n連屋企附近幼稚園啲豆釘都係講普通話<br />\n聽到都心痛"},{"pid":"9dd07c16bbf7b770e2bb7b3d0986df62875c7857","tid":772760,"uid":43655,"like":131,"dislike":4,"score":127,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-09T04:36:49.000Z","msg":"明明係香城中國銀行<br />\nhong shing bank of china<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n喂我屌你老母呀匯豐係hsbc都唔撚識，返屋企食屎啦"},{"pid":"097689199bb0e4bf9b07f93b4cf669242875ff8e","tid":772760,"uid":26332,"like":8,"dislike":0,"score":8,"quote":{"pid":"f5a1088f405671cb597036055696378b7b4c37a3","tid":772760,"uid":28604,"like":58,"dislike":1,"score":57,"quote":{"pid":"fdc81f36cf19a26a18c6467ad7e9126c65f6d6ca","tid":772760,"uid":26332,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2018-08-09T04:28:05.000Z","msg":"事源呢個post<br />\n<br />\n原來HSBC=hang seng bank coporation, 仲令我無咗兩百蚊<br />\n<a href=\"https://lih.kg/772614\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://lih.kg/772614</a><br />\n- 分享自 LIHKG 討論區<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nHSBC 係滙豐根本等於 1+1=2 係常識，係正常人都唔會唔識，但竟然都可以討論，仲有班垃圾屌返人<br />\n<br />\n劣幣驅逐良幣，有一班垃圾支那新移民日日來香港，一班被同化左既垃圾00後，一班低智商垃圾香港人，你話香港仲有無得救？<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/big/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-08-09T04:32:34.000Z","msg":"冇啦 有得救我地唔洗係到討論<br />\n五毛又多 親中拎著數嘅人又多<br />\n連屋企附近幼稚園啲豆釘都係講普通話<br />\n聽到都心痛"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-09T04:37:12.000Z","msg":"支那人真係無一個係無辜"},{"pid":"04b83bf90ae8f3c51201044c790f31d13d1fbfba","tid":772760,"uid":26332,"like":32,"dislike":1,"score":31,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-09T04:42:46.000Z","msg":"有邊個屌個post樓主，邊個就係垃圾"},{"pid":"190b95f87861721f75b09c03f9b24b53858ec0cc","tid":772760,"uid":64590,"like":5,"dislike":3,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-09T04:43:07.000Z","msg":"After the British established Hong Kong as a colony in the aftermath of the First Opium War, merchants from other parts of the British Empire, now in Hong Kong, felt the need for a bank to finance the growing trade, through Hong Kong, and sometimes also through Shanghai, between China and British India, and the rest of the British Empire, and also the rest of Europe, of goods, produces and merchandises of all kinds, but especially of opium, cultivated in or transited (re-exported) through the Raj, and to that end, they organised amongst themselves and <strong>formed The Hongkong and Shanghai Bank in Hong Kong (March 1865)</strong>, and in Shanghai a one-month later.<br />\n<br />\nThe founder, Thomas Sutherland of the Peninsular and Oriental Steam Navigation Company, wanted a bank operating on &quot;sound Scottish banking principles.&quot; Still, the original location of the bank was considered crucial and the founders chose Wardley House in Hong Kong since the construction was based on some of the best feng shui in Colonial Hong Kong. The bank initially leased its premises for HK$500 a month in 1864.<br />\n<br />\nAfter raising a capital stock of HK$5 million, the bank commenced operations on 3 March 1865. It opened a branch in Shanghai during April of that year, and started issuing locally denominated banknotes in both the Crown Colony and Shanghai soon afterwards. The bank was incorporated in Hong Kong as The Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corporation by the Hongkong and Shanghai Bank Ordinance (Numbers 2 and 5 of 1866), and a branch in Japan was also established in Yokohama in 1866. Shares of the bank were one of 13 securities initially traded on the Shanghai Stock Exchange, and were traded on that exchange until its closure by the Japanese closed the exchange in 1941. The bank handled the first public loan in China in 1874, thereafter issuing most public loans."},{"pid":"dbc4243e4d813beedd09b5676a843cd918272153","tid":772760,"uid":198400,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-09T04:47:32.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/